RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 68. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR MINNESOTA BRED WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SEEKING SPLENDOR raced in the three path around the first turn, led the way up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the two path and held clear to the wire. BLACK LIMO raced into traffic in the two path headed into the first turn, bumping several times with TIGER HUNTER and being forced to check in the process, settled in to track the leader on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the far bend in the three path and kept on in the lane. UNIQUE PATH raced in the two path early, stalked the pace setter on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the second turn from the three path, switched to the inside in upper stretch and chased the leader home from there. TIGER HUNTER raced in tight quarters while saving ground around the first turn, bumping with BLACK LIMO several times and checking as a result, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the inside, navigated the far bend from the three and four path and was outkicked in the stretch. EYE ON DESSERT trailed the field the entire way around the oval, raced in the two path throughout and was never a factor. THE RIDER OF HORSE FOUR, UNIQUE PATH, CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST HORSE FIVE, SEEKING SPLENDOR, CITING INTERFERENCE AT THE TOP OF THE STRETCH. UPON REVIEW, NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 2 1M Turf CR: 87. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $10,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since May 11 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claiming Races For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $15,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 1 Mile on the main trac k.) (Rail at 15 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DIPLOMATICA led the field while saving ground around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far bend and dug in in the lane to gamely hold his margin to the wire. FAST TO FORTUNE saved ground around the first bend, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the second bend from the two path, challenged the leader in upper stretch and could not go by that rival, chasing her home from there. RENTAL POOL raced in the two path early, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, began to improve position while saving ground around the second turn and kept on in the lane. LILA'S LUCKY LADY hopped up leaving the gate, bumping with the horse to her inside in the process, saved ground at the back of the pack through the opening half mile, continued to save ground around the far bend and made no bid. RABBIT TWENTY TWO bumped mildly with the horse to her outside at the start, saved ground around the first turn, raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch and around the second bend and never threatened. WEST SIDE GIRL bumped with the horses to both sides leaving the gate, pulled up headed into the first turn and was vanned off after walking soundly onto the van.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 3 1M Dirt CR: 91. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $10,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since May 11 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Pric e $10,000 (Claiming Races For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOMENT saved ground around the first turn, dueled on the inside up the backstretch, shook clear while racing in the two path around the far turn and held that margin in the lane. EISENSTAEDT raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the three path, began a bid approaching the quarter pole and kept on to the finish, no match for the winner. SMART CALL saved ground early, tracked the leaders on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the second bend from the two path and was outkicked in the stretch. RUN LEA RUN raced in the three path around the first bend, settled off the pace on the inside for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the far turn and made no bid. FREDONIAN raced in the two path around the first turn, pressed the pace on the outside up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the four path and tired in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 4 5F Turf CR: 92. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 28000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, TRIAL OR STATE BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $16,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Si nce May 11 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $25,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 5 Furlongs on the main track.) (Rail at 15 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BODENHEIMER dueled on the inside up the backstretch, continued to battle while saving ground around the turn and kicked clear in the lane. RELEASED dueled between horses early, continued to battle from the two path around the bend, could not go with the winner entering the stretch and chased that rival home from there. SAMURAI MIKE trailed the field up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn, began a bid approaching the quarter pole and gained ground late. FUTURE PERFECT raced in the middle of the pack between horses through the opening quarter of a mile, came around the turn in the two path and finished evenly. LONELY PRIVATE raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and finished evenly. BAYOU COLONEL raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the early going, navigated the turn from the three path and showed no kick. MACHO ROCCO dueled on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the turn and tired in the stretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Macho Rocco
ENTRY.OWNER: Big Dog Racing Thiel John F and Thiel Libbie E

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 70. Maiden Claiming Purse 16000. FOR MN-BRED MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PROTONIC AND GIN bumped with the horse to his inside leaving the gate, recovered to chase the leader up the backstretch, came around the turn in the two path, began a bid approaching the quarter pole and kicked clear in the lane. JOSE PATIO dueled on the inside up the backstretch, led the way while saving ground around the bend, was caught in upper stretch and chased the winner home from there. R VOO'S TABOO pressed the pace on the outside early, raced in the three path around the turn and was outkicked in the stretch but kept on to the wire. REJECTION HURTS raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, saved ground around the turn and finished evenly. B L'S CONCERTO dueled between horses up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and faded in the lane. CHARISMO trailed the field through the opening stages, saved ground around the turn and made no bid. KA POW bumped with the horse to his inside at the break, settled in the middle of the pack for the run up the backstretch, began to drop back while racing in the two path around the turn and was empty in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 69. Maiden Claiming Purse 10500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JERUSALEMA (IRE) chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the three path, began a bid nearing the quarter pole, dueled in tight quarters, brushing with GRANDIOSE SUMMER in upper stretch and continued to battle to the wire to just get the win. GRANDIOSE SUMMER raced in the middle of the pack through the opening quarter of a mile, challenged from the two path coming around the bend, brushed lightly with JERUSALEMA in upper stretch and dueled with that rival to the finish, just missing. PAT'S GAL raced in the middle of the pack on the inside early, navigated the turn from the three path and chased the top two home from there. DIXIE GIRL TO tracked the pace setter on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the bend in the four path and faded in the lane. MIZZEN GEE MA led the way up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and tired in the stretch. DR Z'S ELSA trailed the field throughout, came around the turn in the two and three path and was never a factor. A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS MADE INTO THE TOP OF THE STRETCH. UPON REVIEW, NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 7 1M Turf CR: 81. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE DECEMBER 11, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MARCH 11 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500 (Claimi ng Races For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility). Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $12,500. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 1 Mile on the main track.) (Rail at 15 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOLDEN GOPHER saved ground around the first turn, tracked the leader on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn, began a bid passing the quarter pole and got up for the win just in time. MIZZANNA raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the leader up the backstretch, challenged from the two path coming around the far turn and dueled between horses to the finish, just missing. CURIOUS INJI hopped up leaving the gate, recovered to lead the way while saving ground around the first turn and up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the far bend and dug in the stretch, narrowly missing. SHES GOT THE POWER saved ground in the middle of the pack through the opening half mile, continued to save ground around the far turn and finished evenly. FAT AND FURIOUS raced in the three path early, stalked the pace setter from the middle of the pack on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the far bend from the two path and weakened in the lane. COME ON SWEET PEA raced off the pace on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued around the far turn still in the two path and was outkicked from there. SHE B GLAMOROUS saved ground early, trailed the field throughout, raced in the two path around the far turn and made no bid.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 8 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 67. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR MN-BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SAINT SARENA led the way on the inside up the backstretch, opened up while racing in the two path around the turn and held clear to the wire. BAILOUT KELA chased the leader on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, navigated the turn from the three path and kept on in the stretch. PICAFLOR raced off the pace up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend improved position in late stretch. JOMAMA SASSY stalked the leaders on the outside early, came around the turn in the three path and was outkicked in the lane. ELLE'S LIL DIVA pressed the pace on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the bend in the four path and faded in the stretch. BARBARA ROHLOFF tracked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the bend and tired in the stretch. ICYWILBURNYEH lost his rider leaving the gate, chased the field for a spell, was caught and walked off. A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS MADE INTO THE START OF THE RACE. UPON REVIEW, IT WAS DETERMINED THAT HORSE TWO, ICYWILBURNYEH, HAD A FAIR BEGINNING AND NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.
